race.comment: CASHBOOK (1) won an Open 2 at Scone and then just missed at Moruya first-up. Was well supported at Bathurst after, but raced flat. He maps well and has been kept on the fresh side. No surprise if he turns the form around. FRISKEE FROG (14) is fast and should make short work of the awkward barrier. He brings a lip defeat from Goulburn and will be better for it. Gets in light with the 3kg claim and has to be considered. SHERIDAN STREET (6) was expected to win first up at Albury but found a couple better. She runs along and first up last preparation she was a comfortable Maiden winner at this track. Uses the low barrier, and an in-form rider stays aboard. TOO DARN SASSY (8) will be better for the fresh effort at the Sapphire Coast and looks an improver.
